===Etymology===
From {{etyl|peo}} {{rfscript|Old Persian Cuneiform}} {{term|ارمينَه|sc=fa-Arab|tr=Armina|lang=peo}} (late 6th century BC), {{etyl|grc}} {{term|Αρμενία|sc=polytonic|tr=Armenia|lang=grc}} (early 5th century BC). The further etymology of the Persian name is uncertain, but may be connected to the {{etyl|akk}} {{term|Armânum|lang=akk}}, {{term|Armanî|lang=akk}} and/or the Biblical ''Minni''. The Old Persian name is an [[exonym]], see [[w:Hayk|Hayk]] for the native name and [[w:Urartu|Urartu]] for the Biblical ''[[Ararat]]''.

